Author:  MONRO
Vol / Page:
Edition:
Quote:  The method of crossing [the Waitaki] is upon a mogi, which is a floating body, somewhat in the shape of a boat, made of bundles of bulrushes tied together, and strengthened by the flowering stem of the flax, called koradi.
Notes:  1844 Monro Notes of a Journey (Nelson Examiner July 20 et seq.) in 1898 Hocken Contributions 240

