Date:  0/0/1898
Source:  Austral English
Author:  MORRiS
Vol / Page:  253
Edition:
Quote:  <i>Korari, n. </i>Often pronounced <i>Koraddy </i>and <i>Koladdy</i>, and spelt variously; the Maori word for the flowering stem of <i>Phormium tenax</i>, J. and G. Forst. (q.v.), generally used for making a mokihi (q.v.). There is a Maori noun, kora, a small fragment; and a verb korari to pluck a twig, or tear it off.
Notes:

